Tunde Oyekola The Kwara State Governor, AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq, on Monday briefed the President. Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), about some developmental challenges he inherited in his state and the steps he had taken to gradually reposition it. A statement by AbdulRazaq’s Chief Press Secretary, Rafiu Ajakaye, explained that the governor held a one-on-one meeting with the President on Monday at the Villa in Abuja. He said the parley was to keep Buhari abreast of the situation he met on the ground especially as regards infrastructural deficits in the areas of water, roads, education, health, and agriculture,. “The governor also told Mr President how he had been tackling challenges such as gradually restoring water in the state capital and other parts of the state,” Ajakaiye said. He said the governor informed Buhari about the payment of various counterpart funds in the health sector, and how he had returned UNICEF to the state after many years. He said the governor told Buhari about the blacklisting of Kwara State by UBEC but that the payment of the N450m debt by his administration had restored the relationship, among many other steps he had taken. Ajakaiye said Buhari commended AbdulRazaq for the ongoing efforts in repositioning the state. “Buhari promised to look into his requests for the development of Kwara and Nigeria as a whole,” the statement added. Copyright PUNCH.
